          "id": "generic_element_set_commutativity.root.generic_element_set_commutativity.proof.root",
          "status": "resolved"
        },
        "source": {
          "text": "Theorem. For sets A and B, A ∩ B = B ∩ A.\n\nProof. Take an arbitrary element x. If x belongs to A∩B, then x belongs to A and to B, so x belongs to B∩A. Conversely, if x belongs to B∩A, then x belongs to B and to A, so x belongs to A∩B.",
          "id": "generic_element_set_commutativity.root.generic_element_set_commutativity",
          "label": "thm:intersection_comm"
        },
        "id": "generic_element_set_commutativity.root.generic_element_set_commutativity",
        "status": "resolved"
      }
    ],
    "title": "Intersection is Commutative"
  }
